{
  "prompt": "A humorous and metaphorical illustration representing the phrase 'blowing ropes on Slack.' Show a digital Slack workspace interface with exaggerated, comical elements—like a giant tube of face cream or frosting exploding across the computer screen, symbolizing extreme over-the-top productivity. Include colorful Slack channels, emoji reactions, and confetti or fireworks, emphasizing absurd celebration of a mundane corporate accomplishment. The overall tone should be playful, surreal, and PG-rated but heavily metaphorical.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A parody corporate slide deck cover titled 'The BUKAKKE Method™: An Innovative Sales Strategy.' The design should look like a professional PowerPoint slide with clean corporate aesthetics: minimal design, blue and white color scheme, with modern fonts and abstract sales graphics. Include playful but subtle elements that suggest the theme (like fluid motion arrows, overflowing funnels, or confetti-style bursts), while still keeping it PG-rated and satirical. The tone should mock serious business presentations while referencing sales intensity and over-the-top performance.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "Slide 2 of a parody corporate presentation titled 'The BUKAKKE Method™.' Title: 'Spray & Slay: The Importance of Reps Hitting Multiple Faces Daily.' Design should look like a real corporate slide with blue and white tones, clean layout, bullet points, and abstract sales visuals. Include humorous, subtle metaphors like arrows hitting target icons, splashy motion graphics, or overlapping sales avatars. Maintain a PG-rated, satirical tone that mimics high-energy sales training presentations while referencing excessive outreach and performance.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "Slide 3 of a parody corporate presentation titled 'The BUKAKKE Method™.' Title: 'Post-Close Wipe Down: Retention Tactics & CRM Sanitation.' The slide should look like a professional business presentation with a clean blue-and-white layout. Include satirical metaphors like soap bubbles, squeaky clean charts, scrubbing brushes on a CRM dashboard, and playful visuals suggesting cleanup after an intense sales session. Keep the tone PG-rated but deeply tongue-in-cheek, reflecting post-sale hygiene and over-the-top deal closing energy.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
